article.headline: Pennsylvania 73, La Salle 65
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Mark Zoller continued his spectacular shooting, scoring a career-high 25 points, and Eric Osmundson added 17 as Penn defeated local rival La Salle 73-65 and gave coach Fran Dunphy his 300th win. Dunphy, Penn's all-time winningest coach, gained the milestone victory against his alma mater. The 1969 La Salle graduate, in his 17th year with the Quakers, now has an overall record of 300-159. Zoller, a 6-foot-7 forward, made 10-of-17 shots, including 4-of-6 from 3-point range. Steven Smith, who fouled out with just over a minute to go, had 23 points and Darnell Harris 14 for La Salle. La Salle (10-7) lost its fifth straight. The teams battled evenly throughout the second half until the Quakers (10-5) took a 59-53 lead on a 3-pointer by Zoller with 6:43 remaining. The Explorers closed to within 66-62 on a 3-point play by Mike St. John with 2:50 left in the game. After a layup by Zoller, Harris made a 3-point shot, cutting the Penn lead to 68-65 with 36 seconds to go, but Steve Danley made one free-throw and Ibby Jaaber two more with 26 seconds left to seal the victory. The game was stopped for several minutes in the second half after a Penn cheerleader was rendered unconscious during a fall. She was taken to the Hospital of the University of Pennsylvania.
